    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Representations of the human skull or skeleton, particularly as associated with the Mexican festival of the Day of the Dead. The possible media include caricatures or satirical drawings, three-dimensional decorative skulls or skeleton figures, or items of confectionery shaped to resemble a human skull.</Note_Text>
